          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA",
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Two stacks containing 21 um thick natural W foils were",
                " irradiated with 15 MeV and one stack with 35 MeV",
                " protons using stack target technique.",
                "The charge was measured in a Faraday-cup type target",
                " holder.",
                "The energy degradation was calculated by using the",
                " semi empirical formula of Andersen and Ziegler (1977).",
                "Samples and monitor foils 12 um Ti were measured",
                " non-destructively.",
                "The final beam intensity and irradiation energy was",
                " determined by using the excitation function of the",
                " natTi(p,x)48V monitor reaction remeasured over the",
                " whole energy range.",
                "All foils were measured without any chemical processing",
                " by using high resolution gamma-ray spectrometry (HPGe)",
                "The measurements of the samples were started about",
                " 1 day after the end of the bombardment and repeated",
                " after 5 days."
              ]
            }
          ],
